headline.main: ITALIANS STRESS BRITISH STRENGTH; After Telling of Firm Axis Stand, They Decline to Give Predictions on Libya BRITISH BOMBINGS GO ON Germans Also Offer No Boasts on the Outcome of Reported Counter-Offensive

lead_paragraph: ROME, Nov. 21 (AP) -- A titanic battle, "the duration of which is not to be foreseen," has burst in full fury in the Libyan desert with the British hurling everything in their arsenal by land, air and sea at Axis forces, Italian war correspondents reported from the North African front tonight.
